Let IPMEM be the Index to Prioritize Medical Equipment Maintenance. Hence, it can be defined by expression 1 as follows:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ IPMEM=\frac{\sum \limits_{i=1}^n{\rho}_i{x}_i}{N} $$\end{document}IPMEM=∑i=1nρixiNwhere xi, is the variable to evaluate, and ρi is the relevance factor of each variable, i = {1, ..., 7}.

The result of IPMEM was confined to the the interval [0, 1] by a normalization factor (N). To calculate N, the maximum admissible value in the domain (Mi) of each variable xi was multiplied by its corresponding relevance factor (ρi), as shown in expression 2:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ N={\sum}_{i=1}^7{\rho}_i{M}_{im\overset{\hbox{'}}{\mathrm{a}}x} $$\end{document}N=∑i=17ρiMima'x

Substituting the corresponding values in the expression 2, we obtain the value of N as follows: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {\displaystyle \begin{array}{l}N={\rho}_1\left({M}_{1 ma\prime x}\right)+{\rho}_2\left({M}_{2 ma\prime x}\right)+{\rho}_3\left({M}_{3 ma\prime x}\right)+{\rho}_4\left({M}_{4 ma\prime x}\right)\\ {}+{\rho}_5\left({M}_{5 ma\prime x}\right)+{\rho}_6\left({M}_{6 ma\prime x}\right)+{\rho}_7\left({M}_{7 ma\prime x}\right)\\ {}N=10(15)+8(10)+7(10)+7(1)+6(10)+5(5)+4(10)\\ {}N=150+80+70+7+60+40+25=432\end{array}} $$\end{document}N=ρ1M1ma′x+ρ2M2ma′x+ρ3M3ma′x+ρ4M4ma′x+ρ5M5ma′x+ρ6M6ma′x+ρ7M7ma′xN=1015+810+710+71+610+55+410N=150+80+70+7+60+40+25=432

Therefore, IPMEM is defined by the expression 3 as follows:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
